--cpu average used (%)
select
  to_timestamp(t1.time_bucket::varchar, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  t1.value tcp_curr_estab,
  t2.value tcp_tw,
  t3.value tcp_alloc,
  t4.value sockets_used,
  t5.value udp_inuse
from meter_vm_tcp_curr_estab t1
inner join meter_vm_tcp_tw t2 on t1.id = t2.id
inner join meter_vm_tcp_alloc t3 on t3.id = t2.id
inner join meter_vm_sockets_used t4 on t4.id = t3.id
inner join meter_vm_udp_inuse t5 on t5.id = t4.id

  t3.value cpu_load_15
from meter_vm_cpu_load1 t1
inner join meter_vm_cpu_load5 t2 on t1.id = t2.id
inner join meter_vm_cpu_load15 t3 on t3.id = t2.id

select
  to_timestamp(dd.time_bucket, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI'),
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 1), 15)::integer hostname_value,
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 2), 18)::integer resolv_value,
  substr(split_part(ap.value, '|', 3), 12)::integer hosts_value
from meter_vm_filesystem_percentage ap
right join (
SELECT to_char(dd, 'YYYYMMDDHH24MI') "time_bucket"
FROM generate_series(
  current_timestamp - '15 minutes'::interval,
  current_timestamp,
  '1 minute'::interval) dd
) dd on (ap.time_bucket = dd.time_bucket::bigint)
